      "author_association" : "NONE",
      "body" : "@jonatack the use case is basically enabling a separate GUI that's powered by `bitcoind` and that is as capable as Bitcoin Core GUI. Of course this `getgeneralinfo` end-point alone doesn't enable that, but it moves us a little bit closer.\r\n\r\nI think there's a general desire to rearchitect the Bitcoin Core GUI so that it is not tightly coupled with the code outside of the `qt/` folder. In that case one obvious solution is to have a GUI that works asynchronously by using RPC with `bitcoind`, as described in [this comment](https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/issues/17395#issuecomment-552166858).",
